{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013Db7mJ1NE8uANkzFwokhxG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working correctly. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**What was configured:**\n\n1. **MinIO Service** — Created the missing `minio` ClusterIP service so `minio.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9000` resolves correctly.\n\n2. **`es-secure-settings` Secret** — Created with `s3.client.default.access_key` and `s3.client.default.secret_key`. Credentials live only in this secret, never in elasticsearch.yml or env vars.\n\n3. **Elasticsearch keystore** — An init container (`setup-es`) was added to the `es-cluster` statefulset. It runs at every pod start and:\n   - Downloads and installs the `repository-s3` plugin into a shared `emptyDir`\n   - Creates the ES keystore and loads the S3 credentials from the secret into it\n   - Copies the complete config (including keystore) to a shared `emptyDir` for the main container\n\n4. **elasticsearch.yml** — Added three non-sensitive S3 client settings: `endpoint`, `protocol: http`, and `path_style_access: true` (required for MinIO's S3-compatible API). No credentials here.\n\n5. **`minio-repo` repository** — Registered as type `s3`, pointing to the `es-backups` bucket using the `default` S3 client.\n\n6. **Snapshot `snapshot-3`** — Completed with `state: SUCCESS`, 2/2 shards snapshotted (both `app-data` and `.geoip_databases` indices), 0 failures."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":830,"cache_read_input_tokens":88735,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":830},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"345750bd-2903-4710-8544-c47b8be95c0c","uuid":"0fb6da19-6142-4a83-8083-0ea919286855","request_id":"req_011CcMjaPzD1eXMr